N:ui-component-patterns
D:Design reusable UI primitives and component APIs before duplicating product UI. Use when the user needs help extracting shared components, defining variants, slots, controlled-vs-uncontrolled boundaries, composition patterns, Storybook coverage, or deciding what belongs in a reusable primitive versus app-local UI.
G:ui-components react typescript composition variants slots reusable frontend
U[4]:
  Extract duplicated UI into a shared primitive or component family
  Design button, modal, dropdown, card, table, or form-field APIs with variants and slots
  Decide between headless primitives, styled wrappers, and product-local components
  Review whether a component API is overfitted, underpowered, or mixing too many responsibilities
S[5]{n,action}:
  1,Decide whether a reusable primitive is justified
  2,Classify the component role before writing props
  3,Define the smallest useful API surface
  4,Choose controlled vs uncontrolled ownership deliberately
  5,Produce the component architecture packet
